FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1775675472
OL,3,CWhat can Starmer achieve in the Gulf?
OL,5,FBut it does not take enormous
OL,6,Fintellectual effort to deduce that the
OL,7,Ffirst set of talks will be with
OL,8,Farguably the most powerful of the Gulf
OL,9,Fleaders, Saudi's crown prince,
OL,10,FMohammed bin Salman (MBS).
OL,12,FThe most pressing question in all
OL,13,FStarmer's meetings, including with
OL,14,FMBS, is whether the ceasefire between
OL,15,FIran and America and Israel can endure
OL,16,Flong enough for there to be meaningful
OL,17,Ftalks on a sustainable peace, which
OL,18,Fare scheduled to start on Friday in
OL,19,FPakistan.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1775675472
OL,3,CWhat can Starmer achieve in the Gulf?
OL,5,FAccording to British sources - and
OL,6,Ffrankly, this won't surprise you - the
OL,7,Fceasefire is real, holding so far and
OL,8,Fvery unstable.
OL,10,FOne source of anxiety is Israel's
OL,11,Fsomewhat ambivalent commitment to it,
OL,12,Fand notably that Prime Minister
OL,13,FNetanyahu is explicit that the hiatus
OL,14,Fdoes not restrict the Israel Defence
OL,15,FForce's aggression in Lebanon.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1775675472
OL,3,CWhat can Starmer achieve in the Gulf?
OL,5,FAnother is that the devolved structure
OL,6,Fof Iran's military, the IRGC, the
OL,7,FIslamic Revolutionary Guard Corps, and
OL,8,Fthe absence of a centralised power
OL,9,Fstructure in Iran brings the risk of
OL,10,Fcontinued sporadic and unlicensed
OL,11,Fattacks by Iranian militia on Gulf
OL,12,Fcountries - and also means that very
OL,13,Ffew shippers of oil, gas and other
OL,14,Fvital commodities will yet take the
OL,15,Frisk of moving their tankers and ships
OL,16,Fthrough the precarious Strait of
OL,17,FHormuz.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1775675472
OL,3,CWhat can Starmer achieve in the Gulf?
OL,5,FAs one intelligence source put it to
OL,6,Fme, Israel's assassination of so many
OL,7,FIranian leaders makes it incredibly
OL,8,Fdifficult to know who is in charge in
OL,9,Fthe country, if anyone.
OL,11,FOn the more positive side though,
OL,12,Fthere may be a little more underlying
OL,13,Fcommon ground between Tehran and
OL,14,FWashington than their public positions
OL,15,Fon their "non-negotiable" aims for any
OL,16,Fpeace settlement would suggest.
OL,26,@wD@JOUwD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
